00:17:15.618 --> 00:17:17.620
There's got to be
a logical explanation for this.

261
00:17:18.246 --> 00:17:20.089
This isn't what you think it is.

262
00:17:21.499 --> 00:17:24.252
Nobody stores cotton candy like this.

263
00:17:24.961 --> 00:17:27.430
What are you talking about?
Of course it is.

264
00:17:27.547 --> 00:17:28.924
Look.

265
00:18:11.465 --> 00:18:12.717
Joe Lombardo.

266
00:18:24.937 --> 00:18:26.439
Down this way.

267
00:18:45.124 --> 00:18:47.252
- Are you OK?
- I think so.

268
00:18:47.376 --> 00:18:48.753
Come on.

269
00:18:48.878 --> 00:18:50.505
Popcorn. Why popcgrn?

270
00:18:50.630 --> 00:18:52.849
Because they're clowns. that's why.

271
00:19:28.042 --> 00:19:29.669
Mike. get me out of here!

272
00:19:35.800 --> 00:19:37.552
Hurry. they're coming!

273
00:20:09.208 --> 00:20:11.051
We have to tell the police.

274
00:20:11.168 --> 00:20:13.296
We're going to run to the police
and tell them there's a bunch of clowns

275
00:20:13.379 --> 00:20:15.381
running around the hills.
killing people with cotton candy?

276
00:20:15.506 --> 00:20:17.429
I have a friend there.

277
00:20:17.550 --> 00:20:19.518
I know he'll believe us.

278
00:20:19.635 --> 00:20:22.013
I don't know. Debbie.
I wouldn't even believe us.

279
00:21:00.426 --> 00:21:01.973
What the heck?

280
00:21:10.895 --> 00:21:14.399
Dave! 0h. my God! Something horrible
has happened! Somebody's been killed!

281
00:21:14.523 --> 00:21:15.991
Wait a second. Debbie.
What happened?

282
00:21:16.108 --> 00:21:18.657
You gotta help us!
There are two people dead!

283
00:21:18.778 --> 00:21:20.951
- Who. Debbie? Who's dead?
- Joe Lombardo. He's dead.

284
00:21:21.071 --> 00:21:22.243
And some old man. too.

285
00:21:22.364 --> 00:21:23.832
Wait a second. guys.
Are you sure about this?

286
00:21:23.949 --> 00:21:25.576
Yes! It... they were hanging there

287
00:21:25.701 --> 00:21:27.703
wrapped up
in these cotton candy things...

288
00:21:27.828 --> 00:21:29.375
<i>these... cocoons.</i>

289
00:21:29.497 --> 00:21:31.591
- Cocoons?
- Yes. cocoons.

290
00:21:31.707 --> 00:21:33.084
You know. cocoons.

291
00:21:33.209 --> 00:21:34.756
All right. everybody calm down.

292
00:21:34.877 --> 00:21:37.255
Look. Debbie.
come inside and explain this to me.

293
00:21:37.379 --> 00:21:38.676
I'd like to help you. but before I can.

294
00:21:38.798 --> 00:21:41.096
I've got to understand
what's going on here myself.

295
00:21:53.229 --> 00:21:56.199
I really need
to get some mascara. OK?

296
00:21:57.358 --> 00:21:59.577
OK. why don't we just go
to the drugstore?

297
00:21:59.693 --> 00:22:01.240
OK. And then we'll go on.

298
00:22:03.531 --> 00:22:04.703
Look.

299
00:22:11.497 --> 00:22:12.544
Cute.

300
00:22:21.131 --> 00:22:22.348
All right. sit down.

301
00:22:23.300 --> 00:22:25.553
Let's start from the beginning. all right?

302
00:22:25.678 --> 00:22:27.271
OK. OK.

303
00:22:27.388 --> 00:22:28.935
We were up at the Top of the World.

304
00:22:29.056 --> 00:22:32.526
and we saw this shooting star.
and we decided to go look for it.

305
00:22:32.643 --> 00:22:36.318
But instead of finding the shooting star.
we saw this... this circus tent.

306
00:22:36.438 --> 00:22:38.941
And that's when we went inside.
and we saw all those people

307
00:22:39.066 --> 00:22:41.615
in those...
those pink cotton candy cocoons.

308
00:22:41.735 --> 00:22:45.160
Dave. it was not a circus tent.
It was something else.

309
00:22:45.281 --> 00:22:47.249
- What? What?
- It was a spaceship.

310
00:22:47.366 --> 00:22:49.835
And there was these things.
these... killer clowns.

311
00:22:49.952 --> 00:22:51.169
and they shot popcorn at us.

312
00:22:51.287 --> 00:22:52.709
We barely got away.

313
00:22:55.708 --> 00:22:58.382
Killer clowns from outer space?

314
00:22:59.128 --> 00:23:00.880
Holy shit.

315
00:23:01.005 --> 00:23:04.009
Dave. we are telling you the truth.
You've got to believe us.

316
00:23:04.133 --> 00:23:05.601
Let me tell you something. honey.

317
00:23:05.718 --> 00:23:08.562
I was just over there.
There's nothing going on.

318
00:23:08.679 --> 00:23:11.273
Excuse me. please.
but we're talking to Dave.

319
00:23:11.390 --> 00:23:13.984
Now. just hold on a second. Mooney.
They say some people are dead.

320
00:23:14.101 --> 00:23:18.277
- Let's hear them out.
- All right. Dave. OK.

321
00:23:18.397 --> 00:23:22.118
Clowns. cotton candy. flying popcorn.

322
00:23:22.234 --> 00:23:25.579
Go ahead. Let them make fools
out of the police department.

323
00:23:25.696 --> 00:23:28.825
I told you. I was just over there!
You going to believe this little tramp?

324
00:23:28.949 --> 00:23:30.872
Come on. Mooney!

325
00:23:30.993 --> 00:23:32.995
I'm handling this. all right?

326
00:23:36.123 --> 00:23:39.468
All right. all right. Debbie.
who's your friend?

327
00:23:39.585 --> 00:23:41.508
Mike. We go to school together.

328
00:23:41.629 --> 00:23:44.428
You two were up
at Top of the World together?

329
00:23:44.965 --> 00:23:46.012
Yeah.

330
00:23:47.468 --> 00:23:49.562
I know you. you little fart.

331
00:23:49.970 --> 00:23:53.270
You hang out
with the Terenzi brothers.

332
00:23:53.390 --> 00:23:56.143
Clowns? I get it.

333
00:23:56.268 --> 00:23:58.566
Another one of their stupid stunts
to sell ice cream

334
00:23:58.687 --> 00:24:01.611
from that goddamn truck
those hoodlums run around in.

335
00:24:01.732 --> 00:24:03.234
Well. now I really believe this.

336
00:24:03.359 --> 00:24:05.157
Well. you better go now. Dave.

337
00:24:05.277 --> 00:24:07.325
before the clowns take over. huh?

338
00:24:07.446 --> 00:24:09.540
And when you get back
from saving the world.

339
00:24:09.657 --> 00:24:10.783
I want a full written report

340
00:24:10.908 --> 00:24:14.082
so I can give it to the chief
when he gets back on Monday.

341
00:24:15.704 --> 00:24:18.253
Look. everything happened
just the way we said.

342
00:24:18.374 --> 00:24:19.796
We are telling you the truth.

343
00:24:19.917 --> 00:24:21.419
All right. all right.

344
00:24:21.543 --> 00:24:22.590
You two come with me.

345
00:24:22.711 --> 00:24:24.088
Come on.

346
00:24:24.213 --> 00:24:26.887
Hurry up. Dave.
Don't let them get away.

347
00:24:27.925 --> 00:24:29.393
Go ahead. Dave...

348
00:24:30.511 --> 00:24:32.559
...make a dummy out of yourself.

349
00:24:33.681 --> 00:24:36.025
But you're not going
to make a dummy out of me.

350
00:24:38.519 --> 00:24:40.021
You. in the back.

351
00:25:48.005 --> 00:25:51.225
Uh... Oh... Um...

352
00:25:55.554 --> 00:25:57.397
Whoa! Oh...

353
00:26:10.402 --> 00:26:11.574
Excuse me.

354
00:26:11.695 --> 00:26:14.118
Oh. Oh. my.

355
00:26:14.239 --> 00:26:15.741
May I help you?

356
00:26:22.539 --> 00:26:24.257
Oh. no!

357
00:26:45.270 --> 00:26:46.738
Oh. no.

358
00:26:50.984 --> 00:26:52.827
All right. we're going up there
to check this out.

359
00:26:52.945 --> 00:26:54.492
First. I'm taking you home. Debbie.

360
00:26:54.613 --> 00:26:57.492
No way.
I'm going back up there with you.

361
00:26:57.616 --> 00:26:59.084
You can't tell me what to do.

362
00:26:59.201 --> 00:27:00.578
Debbie. just listen to me. would you?

363
00:27:00.702 --> 00:27:02.625
I don't have to listen to you.

364
00:27:02.746 --> 00:27:05.169
You are not
my boyfriend anymore. all right?

365
00:27:05.290 --> 00:27:07.668
Yeah. that's right.
I'm not your boyfriend anymore.

366
00:27:07.793 --> 00:27:10.296
That doesn't change
the way I feel about you. though.

367
00:27:10.420 --> 00:27:12.468
Dave. please.

368
00:27:12.589 --> 00:27:14.683
Don't do this to me.

369
00:27:14.800 --> 00:27:16.643
All right. Debbie. you got a choice.

370
00:27:16.760 --> 00:27:18.012
Either go home.
or I'm going to take you

371
00:27:18.137 --> 00:27:20.981
back to the station and lock you up
for safekeeping. How's that?

372
00:27:25.519 --> 00:27:26.987
Pizza!

373
00:27:28.647 --> 00:27:30.775
Oh. Pizza.

374
00:27:30.899 --> 00:27:33.402
Uh-huh.

375
00:27:49.334 --> 00:27:52.087
- For you.
- Oh! For me?

376
00:27:53.172 --> 00:27:54.549
Oh!

377
00:27:54.673 --> 00:27:58.678
Oh. Jim... is this from you?

378
00:27:59.553 --> 00:28:01.351
<i>- Huh?
' on!</i>

379
00:28:09.563 --> 00:28:11.031
Look. Debbie...

380
00:28:11.565 --> 00:28:13.909
May I please speak to Mike outside?

381
00:28:15.485 --> 00:28:17.954
Fine. Sure.

382
00:28:18.071 --> 00:28:19.414
Thank you.

383
00:28:28.332 --> 00:28:29.709
Your old boyfriend? This is great.

384
00:28:29.833 --> 00:28:31.631
Will you come here?

385
00:28:33.670 --> 00:28:36.093
He's probably going to take me up
on top of the hill and shoot me.

386
00:28:36.215 --> 00:28:37.967
Look. don't worry about Dave.

387
00:28:38.091 --> 00:28:41.470
It's those clowns
you got to worry about.

388
00:28:41.595 --> 00:28:45.441
Listen. as soon as you guys leave here.
I'm going to follow you guys up there.

389
00:28:45.557 --> 00:28:46.774
You're going
to follow us up there?

390
00:28:46.892 --> 00:28:49.315
Debbie. I don't even
want to go up there.

391
00:28:49.436 --> 00:28:51.780
Listen. you stay inside the house
and keep the door locked.

392
00:28:51.897 --> 00:28:54.525
I'll be back here in a little bit
to check on you.

393
00:28:55.525 --> 00:28:56.526
OK?

394
00:28:58.403 --> 00:28:59.871
You better.

395
00:29:09.706 --> 00:29:11.458
That's good timing.

396
00:29:43.323 --> 00:29:45.041
Oh!

397
00:29:54.668 --> 00:29:56.591
Oh!

398
00:30:17.274 --> 00:30:18.821
Wait a minute.

399
00:30:19.818 --> 00:30:21.161
Where is it?

400
00:30:21.278 --> 00:30:22.621
Yeah. that's what I'd like to know. pal.

401
00:30:22.738 --> 00:30:24.331
It was right there where that hole is.

402
00:30:24.448 --> 00:30:25.700
So are you saying that hole
is where the tent was?

403
00:30:25.824 --> 00:30:27.576
The tent made that hole...
is that what you're telling me?

404
00:30:27.701 --> 00:30:29.123
Yes! It was there.

405
00:30:29.244 --> 00:30:30.496
Look. we saw it.
That's a fact.

406
00:30:30.620 --> 00:30:32.247
I'll tell you what the facts are. mister.

407
00:30:32.372 --> 00:30:34.841
You said people are being killed.
Now. where are the bodies?

408
00:30:34.958 --> 00:30:36.676
I don't know.
I saw Joe Lombardo dead.

409
00:30:36.793 --> 00:30:38.010
I can only tell you what I think I saw.

410
00:30:38.128 --> 00:30:39.880
Oh. so now you just think you saw?

411
00:30:40.005 --> 00:30:41.177
No! I know what I saw.

412
00:30:41.298 --> 00:30:42.891
I just can't prove it. My proof is gone.

413
00:30:43.008 --> 00:30:44.180
Yeah. right. Turn around. pal.

414
00:30:45.886 --> 00:30:47.354
Mooney was right. huh?

415
00:30:47.471 --> 00:30:49.144
Got nothing better to do
but cause problems.

416
00:30:49.264 --> 00:30:50.732
Well. you're not going
to get away with it this time.

417
00:30:50.849 --> 00:30:53.318
Get away with what?
Debbie saw it. too.

418
00:30:53.435 --> 00:30:55.153
- Yeah. she did. didn't she?
- Ow!

419
00:30:55.270 --> 00:30:56.317
Come on.

420
00:31:01.068 --> 00:31:02.786
Hey. Eddie. is that a new bike you got?

421
00:31:02.903 --> 00:31:04.621
What's happening. Spike?

422
00:31:15.207 --> 00:31:17.460
on!

423
00:31:17.584 --> 00:31:20.428
Big bad Jojo comin' into town.

424
00:31:21.296 --> 00:31:22.468
Watch this. baby.

425
00:31:22.589 --> 00:31:24.262
Is that bike too big for you?

426
00:31:24.383 --> 00:31:25.851
Hey. Patty!

427
00:31:29.179 --> 00:31:30.396
Mean bike you got there.

428
00:31:30.514 --> 00:31:31.811
Yeah.

429
00:31:33.809 --> 00:31:37.780
- Can I take a ride. pal?
- Uh-uh!

430
00:31:39.606 --> 00:31:41.449
Can I beep the horn?

431
00:31:41.566 --> 00:31:43.193
Mm-hm.

432
00:31:44.444 --> 00:31:47.539
Oh. thank you!

433
00:31:53.203 --> 00:31:56.798
He should've let the man
ride his bike.

434
00:32:00.377 --> 00:32:04.678
I'm sorry.
I seem to have broken your bike.

435
00:32:09.261 --> 00:32:10.433
Where'd he go?

436
00:32:12.973 --> 00:32:14.896
Put up your dukes. put up your dukes!

437
00:32:25.360 --> 00:32:28.705
What are you going to do.
knock my block off?

438
00:32:31.074 --> 00:32:32.451
Damn!

439
00:32:34.035 --> 00:32:35.912
Hey. come on. let's get out of here!

440
00:32:36.037 --> 00:32:37.084
Come on. guys!

441
00:32:37.205 --> 00:32:38.206
Get me out of here!

442
00:32:47.883 --> 00:32:50.432
Here's some more ketchup
for your French fries.

443
00:32:50.552 --> 00:32:51.849
Now. here's some more ketchup.

444
00:32:51.970 --> 00:32:54.439
I want you to sit still
and eat your hamburger.

445
00:32:54.556 --> 00:32:56.775
You know.
this isn't as much fun as it used to be.

446
00:32:56.892 --> 00:32:58.769
It is if you're the winners.

447
00:34:00.205 --> 00:34:01.502
Back here. young lady.

448
00:34:01.623 --> 00:34:03.751
You're not going anywhere
until you finish your food.

449
00:34:24.771 --> 00:34:26.444
What's going on?

450
00:36:10.126 --> 00:36:11.628
All right. get out.

451
00:36:15.215 --> 00:36:16.717
Turn around.

452
00:36:16.841 --> 00:36:18.593
What are you doing. man?

453
00:36:18.718 --> 00:36:19.765
You're not going to hit me. are you?

454
00:36:19.886 --> 00:36:21.763
Just turn around. pal. all right?

455
00:36:21.888 --> 00:36:23.185
Look. I'm sorry about Debbie. but I...

456
00:36:23.306 --> 00:36:24.728
Just drop it. Mike!

457
00:36:29.646 --> 00:36:31.114
Check this out.

458
00:36:32.065 --> 00:36:33.362
That's the stuff.

459
00:36:33.483 --> 00:36:34.700
That's the stuff
that I was telling you about

460
00:36:34.818 --> 00:36:36.661
that was all wrapped
around Joe Lombardo.

461
00:36:36.778 --> 00:36:37.745
Where'd you get that?

462
00:36:37.862 --> 00:36:39.489
Over in that Jeep over there.

463
00:36:40.365 --> 00:36:42.163
- That's McReed's Jeep.
- Who's McReed?

464
00:36:42.283 --> 00:36:44.661
Bob McReed. He was up here tonight
with me and Debbie.

465
00:36:45.328 --> 00:36:49.253
Those are his glasses.
They got him. He's dead.

466
00:37:04.013 --> 00:37:05.765
Crescent Cove police station.
Mooney speaking.

467
00:37:05.890 --> 00:37:07.517
'I'd like to report a disturbance.'

468
00:37:07.642 --> 00:37:09.861
Wait a minute. Calm down.
I can't understand you.

469
00:37:09.978 --> 00:37:11.525
- 'Clowns!'
- What?

470
00:37:11.646 --> 00:37:13.990
'They're at my front door!
They're destroying property!'

471
00:37:14.107 --> 00:37:15.529
Clowns. huh?

472
00:37:16.359 --> 00:37:18.236
And now they're at your front door. huh?

473
00:37:18.361 --> 00:37:19.863
'They're at my front door right now!'

474
00:37:19.988 --> 00:37:21.080
Wait a minute. Who is this?

475
00:37:21.197 --> 00:37:23.450
'Would you just get over here?'

476
00:37:24.659 --> 00:37:27.503
Stupid kids and their pranks.

477
00:37:31.541 --> 00:37:33.043
Rich little bastards.

478
00:37:34.127 --> 00:37:35.845
I'd shoot them all.

479
00:37:37.756 --> 00:37:40.350
Daddy sends them
to fancy schools...

480
00:37:41.468 --> 00:37:44.517
...so the police department
can babysit the little pricks.

481
00:37:53.938 --> 00:37:56.066
Police station.
Mooney speaking. Yeah.

482
00:37:57.233 --> 00:37:58.826
Hello. Curt?

483
00:37:59.486 --> 00:38:02.490
I think I have a bit of a problem here.

484
00:38:06.951 --> 00:38:09.704
Oh... Just a minute.

485
00:38:09.829 --> 00:38:11.752
Jesus. not you. too. Mr. Myers.

486
00:38:14.125 --> 00:38:16.503
Police station. Mooney here.
What?

487
00:38:16.628 --> 00:38:18.630
'They took my wife... the clowns...'

488
00:38:18.755 --> 00:38:21.099
Oh. They took your wife away
in a balloon?

489
00:38:21.216 --> 00:38:24.015
Well. you don't need the police. pal.
You need a psychiatrist!

490
00:38:26.471 --> 00:38:28.314
<i>Mr. Myers?</i>

491
00:38:30.725 --> 00:38:33.569
Do the Terenzi brothers
have the whole town in on this?

492
00:38:36.314 --> 00:38:38.408
Well. to hell with them all.

493
00:38:42.612 --> 00:38:44.580
They wanna play games.

494
00:38:44.697 --> 00:38:46.825
they're messing with the wrong guy.

495
00:38:56.000 --> 00:38:58.549
<i>_ Huh?</i>

496
00:38:58.670 --> 00:38:59.967
Jesus! Oh. no!

497
00:39:00.088 --> 00:39:02.511
Oh. no! Come on. Joe. get going!

498
00:39:09.055 --> 00:39:11.103
<i>' God!</i>

499
00:41:58.016 --> 00:42:00.986
I'll call the state police
up at Marlborough. They've got a lab.

500
00:42:01.102 --> 00:42:03.571
Maybe somebody up there
can tell us what this stuff is.

501
00:42:03.688 --> 00:42:05.486
It's not cotton candy. that's for sure.

502
00:42:05.982 --> 00:42:08.906
Yes. Finally.
That's what I've been telling you.

503
00:42:10.945 --> 00:42:14.165
Look. I'm sorry
I was a little tough on you back there.

504
00:42:14.991 --> 00:42:16.584
It's been a hard night.

505
00:42:18.286 --> 00:42:21.039
Having Debbie involved
just makes it a lot more difficult.

506
00:42:21.164 --> 00:42:22.541
What can I say? I didn't know...

507
00:42:22.665 --> 00:42:25.544
It's got nothing to do with you. really.
It's me.

508
00:42:26.377 --> 00:42:28.596
It's obvious she goes for laughs.
not stability.

509
00:42:55.448 --> 00:42:58.452
Oh!

510
00:43:00.328 --> 00:43:01.375
- Boo.
- Oh...

511
00:43:01.496 --> 00:43:04.796
Oh. my God.

512
00:43:35.655 --> 00:43:38.625
You can just drop me off
over here. I'll take the bus home.

513
00:43:38.741 --> 00:43:42.086
No way. Remember.
you're the one who's seen these things.

514
00:43:43.246 --> 00:43:44.793
Look! A clown! Right there!

515
00:43:49.252 --> 00:43:51.505
There he is. I told you.
Will you get out there and shoot him?

516
00:43:51.629 --> 00:43:53.882
- Get him. Dave. Kill him.
- Hang on. Mike.

517
00:43:54.006 --> 00:43:55.633
Calm down. Let me check this out.

518
00:44:12.066 --> 00:44:14.364
- Holy shit!
- I don't believe it.

519
00:44:21.617 --> 00:44:24.040
- Dave. run it down!
- Mike. let go! Mike! Mike!

520
00:44:30.209 --> 00:44:32.553
What are you doing?
You could've gotten us killed!

521
00:44:32.670 --> 00:44:35.594
I'm sorry.
I freaked out a little bit.

522
00:44:35.715 --> 00:44:37.092
Where is he?

523
00:44:45.850 --> 00:44:48.820
I don't know.
I don't see him anywhere.

524
00:44:51.772 --> 00:44:53.149
He's gone.

525
00:44:53.608 --> 00:44:55.485
He went straight up.

526
00:44:56.319 --> 00:44:57.411
I've seen enough.

527
00:44:58.863 --> 00:45:01.082
One Baker five.
Curt. do you read me? Over.

528
00:45:01.866 --> 00:45:05.166
One Baker five.
This is Mooney speaking.

529
00:45:05.286 --> 00:45:07.163
I was a little worried about you.

530
00:45:07.288 --> 00:45:10.633
I thought the big bad clowns
got a hold of you. Over.

531
00:45:10.750 --> 00:45:13.253
Mooney. I want you to listen to me
and don't say anything.

532
00:45:13.377 --> 00:45:15.004
I want you to call the state police
and get help.

533
00:45:15.129 --> 00:45:18.804
There are clowns.
and they are killing people. Over.

534
00:45:18.925 --> 00:45:20.552
OK. let me get this straight.

535
00:45:20.676 --> 00:45:23.680
You say there are clowns.
and you've seen them.

536
00:45:23.804 --> 00:45:25.556
OK. Dave. that's it.

537
00:45:25.681 --> 00:45:28.059
Screw you and your college flunkies.

538
00:45:28.184 --> 00:45:30.357
I've had enough of this from you
and from everyone else.

539
00:45:30.478 --> 00:45:32.572
I know what you guys are trying to do:

540
00:45:32.688 --> 00:45:34.907
break me down.
drive me out of the force.

541
00:45:35.024 --> 00:45:37.743
Well. it's going to take a hell of a lot more
than a lame prank like this

542
00:45:37.860 --> 00:45:43.082
to get Curtis Mooney to throw in
his badge. so fuck you! Over.

543
00:45:43.199 --> 00:45:46.043
Mooney. this is an emergency.
Mooney!

544
00:45:46.869 --> 00:45:50.339
He cut me off.
That son of a bitch cut me off!

545
00:45:50.456 --> 00:45:52.550
I got to get...
I got to get back to the station.

546
00:45:52.667 --> 00:45:55.671
I don't know what I'm going to say.
but I got to get through to the state police.

547
00:45:57.129 --> 00:45:59.427
Paul. get the truck!
What about the girls?

548
00:45:59.548 --> 00:46:01.471
Forget about the girls.
They eat too much.

549
00:46:01.592 --> 00:46:02.889
They didn't pay for the ice cream!

550
00:46:03.010 --> 00:46:04.603
So what?
The truck's getting away!

551
00:46:04.720 --> 00:46:06.688
Hey. those aren't killer clowns.
Those are the Terenzi brothers.

552
00:46:06.806 --> 00:46:08.058
Terenzi brothers?

553
00:46:08.182 --> 00:46:09.604
Get back to the station. Radio for help.

554
00:46:09.725 --> 00:46:11.477
I'll catch up with my friends.
try to warn people.

555
00:46:11.602 --> 00:46:13.730
Tell everyone to stay indoors
and don't do anything stupid.

556
00:46:13.854 --> 00:46:14.946
You. too.

557
00:46:22.196 --> 00:46:23.618
- Oh. shit.
- You idiot!

558
00:46:23.739 --> 00:46:24.911
Don't yell at me!
You were driving!

559
00:46:25.032 --> 00:46:26.579
Can't you just do one thing right?

560
00:46:26.701 --> 00:46:28.954
This whole ice cream thing
was your idea.

561
00:46:29.078 --> 00:46:31.080
My idea?
You said we'd get girls this way.

562
00:46:31.205 --> 00:46:32.331
No. I didn't. You did.

563
00:46:32.456 --> 00:46:34.458
- You did.
- You did.

564
00:46:34.583 --> 00:46:35.880
You did.

565
00:46:37.003 --> 00:46:38.755
Hey. Rich. Paul!

566
00:46:38.879 --> 00:46:40.927
Oh. man. am I glad to see you guys.

567
00:46:41.048 --> 00:46:42.595
Mike. how you doing?
You want some ice cream?

568
00:46:42.717 --> 00:46:43.809
No. no. man. listen.

569
00:46:43.926 --> 00:46:45.599
Something horrible has happened.
I need your help.

570
00:46:45.720 --> 00:46:47.097
- What are you talking about?
- What's wrong?

571
00:46:47.221 --> 00:46:48.689
There's no time to explain.

572
00:46:48.806 --> 00:46:50.649
There's clowns going around
killing people.

573
00:46:51.767 --> 00:46:52.893
Ha!

574
00:46:53.019 --> 00:46:55.772
Tonight. Debbie and I
were up on the Top of the World.

575
00:46:55.896 --> 00:46:58.194
and we followed this spaceship.
and there were these...

576
00:46:58.316 --> 00:47:00.910
there were these clowns
carrying cotton candy cocoons

577
00:47:01.027 --> 00:47:04.247
and they were shooting
these... these popcorn guns.

578
00:47:04.363 --> 00:47:06.491
And there's...
there's a circus tent spaceship. right?

579
00:47:06.615 --> 00:47:08.288
But it's not there anymore.
but we were there.

580
00:47:08.409 --> 00:47:09.535
We saw the whole thing.

581
00:47:09.660 --> 00:47:12.664
And they say we're crazy. So?

582
00:47:12.788 --> 00:47:14.665
Oh. come on. you guys.
I'm not fooling around.

583
00:47:14.790 --> 00:47:17.964
Mike. what do you want us to do?
We have ice cream to sell tonight.

584
00:47:18.085 --> 00:47:19.678
Paul. this is more important
than selling ice cream.

585
00:47:19.795 --> 00:47:22.173
There's clowns going around
killing people. We're all in danger.

586
00:47:22.673 --> 00:47:24.767
Well. we haven't sold
that much ice cream tonight.

587
00:47:24.884 --> 00:47:25.931
We haven't sold any.

588
00:47:26.052 --> 00:47:27.770
Come on. guys. will you help me?

589
00:47:27.887 --> 00:47:29.605
At least take me over
to Debbie's house. OK?

590
00:47:29.722 --> 00:47:30.814
I think she's in danger.

591
00:47:31.849 --> 00:47:33.066
Does she have any roommates?

592
00:47:34.393 --> 00:47:37.146
Yes. She's got two.
She's got two beautiful roommates

593
00:47:37.271 --> 00:47:38.898
with big boobs.

594
00:47:39.023 --> 00:47:40.240
Do they like ice cream?

595
00:47:40.358 --> 00:47:41.530
They love it.

596
00:47:42.485 --> 00:47:45.364
What are we waiting for?

597
00:47:45.488 --> 00:47:47.035
Come on!

598
00:47:48.115 --> 00:47:50.209
You guys. get out of the way.

599
00:47:55.414 --> 00:47:57.166
Frig youse all.

600
00:47:58.084 --> 00:47:59.961
You ain't going to get the best of me.

601
00:48:06.258 --> 00:48:09.387
I made it through Korea.
I can make it through this bullshit.

602
00:48:26.237 --> 00:48:27.489
Well...

603
00:48:27.947 --> 00:48:30.416
Whoop dee goddamn dee do.

604
00:48:30.533 --> 00:48:32.251
What do we have here?

605
00:48:42.044 --> 00:48:45.674
Well. son.
I think you made a big mistake.

606
00:48:45.798 --> 00:48:48.017
You're in Mooney's territory now.

607
00:48:50.594 --> 00:48:52.141
For me?

608
00:49:01.981 --> 00:49:03.824
I ought to shoot you right now.

609
00:49:03.941 --> 00:49:06.069
you red-nosed freak.

610
00:49:06.610 --> 00:49:09.113
So you want to play games. eh?

611
00:49:19.832 --> 00:49:21.379
Turn around!

612
00:49:26.839 --> 00:49:28.182
All right.

613
00:49:29.341 --> 00:49:31.639
I'm supposed to read you your rights.

614
00:49:31.760 --> 00:49:33.888
but you're in Mooney's jail...

615
00:49:35.014 --> 00:49:37.392
...and you ain't got no rights.

616
00:49:37.516 --> 00:49:39.393
All right. buster.

617
00:49:40.144 --> 00:49:41.487
God.

618
00:49:49.820 --> 00:49:51.618
Officer Mooney.
come on. let us out of here.

619
00:49:51.739 --> 00:49:53.161
Are we going to be here all night?

620
00:49:53.282 --> 00:49:54.454
We get one phone call. don't we?

621
00:49:54.575 --> 00:49:56.828
- Right. I'm going to call my...
- Shut up!

622
00:50:08.214 --> 00:50:09.807
Get your hands up.

623
00:50:32.530 --> 00:50:34.157
Get in there.

624
00:50:52.841 --> 00:50:55.094
I don't know who you are.

625
00:50:55.219 --> 00:50:57.563
but before this night's over.

626
00:50:58.305 --> 00:51:00.273
you're going to be begging for mercy.

627
00:51:17.741 --> 00:51:19.414
What are you in for?

628
00:51:44.977 --> 00:51:47.105
<i>Mooney!</i>

629
00:51:50.733 --> 00:51:53.657
Police department. Hello?

630
00:52:46.413 --> 00:52:47.630
Mooney?

631
00:52:48.499 --> 00:52:50.467
Mooney. you back here?

632
00:53:41.552 --> 00:53:43.020
Oh. God.

633
00:54:29.725 --> 00:54:31.102
Hey. Dave.

634
00:54:31.810 --> 00:54:34.689
who was the lady I saw you with
last night?

635
00:54:45.657 --> 00:54:47.284
Don't worry. Dave.

636
00:54:49.119 --> 00:54:51.588
All we want to do is kill you.

637
00:55:44.383 --> 00:55:46.511
'C.C.P.D..
this is Marlborough State Police.'

638
00:55:46.635 --> 00:55:48.979
'Dave. Curt. are you there? Over.'

639
00:55:49.096 --> 00:55:50.348
Jack. Jack. we need your assistance.

640
00:55:50.472 --> 00:55:52.816
The town's gone crazy.
People are being killed. Over.

641
00:55:52.933 --> 00:55:55.777
'What's all these reports
about circus clowns?'

642
00:55:56.436 --> 00:55:58.905
These clowns aren't people.
They're some kind of creatures.

643
00:55:59.022 --> 00:56:00.649
things from another planet.

644
00:56:00.774 --> 00:56:04.028
Jack. they're killing people.
Officer Mooney is dead.

645
00:56:04.152 --> 00:56:06.701
I know. I saw it.
He was killed by one of these things.

646
00:56:06.822 --> 00:56:09.746
Could you send all available units
immediately. please? Over.

647
00:56:11.159 --> 00:56:12.627
Come on. Jack!

648
00:56:16.164 --> 00:56:19.418
'OK. calm down. buddy.
Help is on the way.'

649
00:56:31.305 --> 00:56:32.807
Debbie.

650
00:56:39.563 --> 00:56:42.066
'Calling all clowns. calling all clowns.

651
00:56:42.190 --> 00:56:43.533
'This is Jojo.

652
00:56:43.650 --> 00:56:46.574
'Are there any space clowns out there?'

653
00:56:46.695 --> 00:56:49.574
You guys. will you stop fooling around?

654
00:56:49.698 --> 00:56:51.666
Look. Mike. come on.

655
00:56:51.783 --> 00:56:54.787
Cocoons.
popcorn guns. monster shadows.

656
00:56:54.912 --> 00:56:57.916
- I mean. what do you think we are?
- We're not as stupid as we look.

657
00:56:58.040 --> 00:57:00.759
This isn't the first wild thing
you've tried to put over on us.

658
00:57:00.876 --> 00:57:02.298
Look. you remember Hidden Lake?

659
00:57:02.419 --> 00:57:05.138
Come on. forget Hidden Lake.
This has nothing to do with Hidden Lake.

660
00:57:05.255 --> 00:57:09.180
We would have to be total morons
to believe this clown invasion crap.

661
00:57:09.301 --> 00:57:11.804
If there are killer clowns
running around here.

662
00:57:11.929 --> 00:57:14.102
then I'm Porky Pig.

663
00:58:07.234 --> 00:58:09.032
Get the hell out of here.

664
00:58:35.512 --> 00:58:36.855
Ah!

665
00:58:55.490 --> 00:58:56.912
Ah!

666
00:59:27.647 --> 00:59:30.321
Debbie. it's Mike. Open up.

667
00:59:30.442 --> 00:59:31.819
Mike?

668
00:59:33.236 --> 00:59:36.285
Debbie. Debbie. Debbie.

669
01:00:22.661 --> 01:00:24.334
OK. see this white house
right over here?

670
01:00:24.454 --> 01:00:26.331
- Take a right... I mean a left right here.
- A left?

671
01:00:26.456 --> 01:00:27.332
- Right.
- Right.

672
01:00:27.457 --> 01:00:28.709
No. left! Left!

673
01:00:37.092 --> 01:00:38.685
The house right up...

674
01:00:40.929 --> 01:00:43.057
Holy shit. What is that?

675
01:00:45.142 --> 01:00:47.019
Uh-oh.

676
01:00:50.522 --> 01:00:52.274
Wow. Look at that.

677
01:00:52.399 --> 01:00:54.948
Mike!

678
01:00:59.239 --> 01:01:01.662
Come on. we can't lose them!
They got Debbie!

679
01:01:16.006 --> 01:01:17.007
Hey. Mike!

680
01:01:26.683 --> 01:01:29.061
Come on. Rich. we're losing them.
Can you go a little bit faster?

681
01:01:29.186 --> 01:01:31.314
Mike. what do you want?
This is an ice cream truck.

682
01:01:45.285 --> 01:01:47.583
Hey. Rich. the cops!
Stop the truck!

683
01:01:47.704 --> 01:01:49.672
Ah!

684
01:01:50.916 --> 01:01:54.011
Shit. Rich. now you did it.

685
01:01:54.127 --> 01:01:55.674
I did it? What do you mean?
You told me to stop.

686
01:01:55.795 --> 01:01:58.890
- I told you to pull over.
- You didn't. You said stop. so I stopped.

687
01:01:59.007 --> 01:02:00.054
I meant pull over.

688
01:02:00.175 --> 01:02:02.098
If you meant pull over.
you should have said pull over.

689
01:02:02.219 --> 01:02:03.892
Why don't you say
what you mean next time?

690
01:02:04.012 --> 01:02:05.764
Come on.
let's go see what happened.

691
01:02:09.142 --> 01:02:10.485
Dave. are you OK?

692
01:02:12.854 --> 01:02:14.151
Oh. God.

693
01:02:14.272 --> 01:02:17.116
Oh. fuck.
What the hell are you guys doing?

694
01:02:17.234 --> 01:02:18.326
They got Debbie.

695
01:02:19.611 --> 01:02:21.033
Get in the truck. pal.

696
01:02:24.074 --> 01:02:27.544
Gee. officer. I'm really sorry.
I was feeling a little queasy.

697
01:02:27.661 --> 01:02:28.708
Which way were they heading?

698
01:02:28.828 --> 01:02:30.330
They went that way.
but now we lost them.

699
01:02:30.455 --> 01:02:31.707
I don't know where they went.

700
01:02:31.831 --> 01:02:34.459
I do. If you were a clown.
where would you hide?

701
01:02:34.584 --> 01:02:35.676
The amusement park!

702
01:02:35.794 --> 01:02:37.967
<i>' Great!
- All right!</i>

703
01:03:10.912 --> 01:03:14.883
The park's closed.
I'll have to ask you to leave.

704
01:03:46.573 --> 01:03:49.918
What are you going to do
with those pies. boys?

705
01:04:39.250 --> 01:04:40.376
Hey. hey. hey!

706
01:04:41.002 --> 01:04:42.219
Everybody stick together.

707
01:04:46.007 --> 01:04:47.179
She's gone.

708
01:04:47.300 --> 01:04:50.725
Wow. Hey. you guys. this is weird.

709
01:04:52.514 --> 01:04:53.936
Look at this stuff.

710
01:04:54.057 --> 01:04:56.435
Looks like a wad of melted ice cream.

711
01:04:56.559 --> 01:04:57.606
Yeah. well. it's not.

712
01:04:57.727 --> 01:04:58.774
Oh. shit.

713
01:04:59.771 --> 01:05:00.988
Yeah.

714
01:05:01.564 --> 01:05:02.690
Come on.

715
01:05:17.664 --> 01:05:20.463
Mike. you take this and follow me.

716
01:05:20.583 --> 01:05:22.301
All right. now. you guys.

717
01:05:22.419 --> 01:05:25.298
no fooling around.
Stick together. OK?

718
01:05:25.797 --> 01:05:27.765
What the hell's in here?

719
01:05:36.516 --> 01:05:39.440
Oh. scary!

720
01:05:39.561 --> 01:05:41.689
Dave. did you get through for help?

721
01:05:41.813 --> 01:05:44.157
Yeah. Yeah. help is on the way.

722
01:05:44.274 --> 01:05:46.447
You tell them it was an invasion?

723
01:05:46.568 --> 01:05:49.321
I told them.
but I don't really believe it myself.

724
01:05:49.446 --> 01:05:50.823
Where did they come from?

725
01:05:50.947 --> 01:05:53.621
Why are they here?
Why. why clowns?

726
01:05:53.741 --> 01:05:55.539
They're not clowns.

727
01:05:55.660 --> 01:05:57.412
They're some kind of animal
from another world

728
01:05:57.537 --> 01:05:59.255
that just look like clowns.

729
01:06:00.623 --> 01:06:02.000
Shit. Dave.

730
01:06:02.125 --> 01:06:04.219
Dave.
maybe they're the ancient astronauts

731
01:06:04.335 --> 01:06:06.508
that came to our planet centuries ago.

732
01:06:06.629 --> 01:06:09.758
and our idea of clowns
just comes from them.

733
01:06:09.883 --> 01:06:11.851
Well. how come they're not funny?

734
01:06:11.968 --> 01:06:13.686
Maybe they're from a dying planet.

735
01:06:13.803 --> 01:06:16.181
Maybe their sun pooped out
and they need a new place to live.

736
01:06:16.306 --> 01:06:20.277
Maybe they're using us
for experiments to dissect and study.

737
01:06:20.393 --> 01:06:22.862
So that means they're intelligent.

738
01:06:22.979 --> 01:06:25.027
So why don't they communicate with us?

739
01:06:25.148 --> 01:06:27.992
I mean. talk to us instead of killing us?

740
01:06:28.109 --> 01:06:30.453
Maybe they're just cruising
through the galaxy

741
01:06:30.570 --> 01:06:33.574
and stopped here for a bite to eat.

742
01:06:36.117 --> 01:06:40.623
Yeah. Look. everybody.
let's just hold off on the talking. OK?

743
01:06:40.747 --> 01:06:42.624
Let's not give ourselves away.

744
01:06:43.750 --> 01:06:45.218
What are we gonna do
when we find them?

745
01:06:45.335 --> 01:06:49.010
- Can we kill 'em?
- Yeah. You shoot 'em in the nose.

746
01:06:58.515 --> 01:07:00.392
Hey. watch this.

747
01:07:02.018 --> 01:07:03.190
Cool.

748
01:07:28.044 --> 01:07:29.421
Whoo!

749
01:07:29.546 --> 01:07:30.672
What happened?

750
01:07:30.797 --> 01:07:33.175
- What did you do?
- I didn't do anything.

751
01:07:33.299 --> 01:07:37.224
Look. don't touch anything. OK?
This place is probably booby-trapped.

752
01:07:42.600 --> 01:07:44.477
All right now.
look you guys. stay together.

753
01:07:44.602 --> 01:07:46.275
I don't want
to have to find you. too.

754
01:07:46.396 --> 01:07:48.569
No problem. We can handle it.

755
01:07:48.690 --> 01:07:50.158
Yeah.

756
01:07:57.657 --> 01:08:00.126
All right. let's go.

757
01:08:00.243 --> 01:08:03.668
Where'd they go?
Come on. Rich. Paul.

758
01:08:04.289 --> 01:08:07.759
Don't worry about the Terenzi brothers.
They do this all the time.

759
01:08:07.875 --> 01:08:11.220
Those guys are like cats.
They always land on their feet.

760
01:08:16.009 --> 01:08:18.512
<i>' oh! Ah!
' Uh!</i>

761
01:08:31.899 --> 01:08:33.697
Are you Debbie's roommates?

762
01:08:34.527 --> 01:08:36.279
Wait a second.

763
01:08:38.072 --> 01:08:39.790
I recognize this place.

764
01:08:41.075 --> 01:08:44.454
